entry.def: Pilings are wooden, concrete, or metal posts which are pushed into the ground and on which buildings or bridges are built. Pilings are often used in very wet areas so that the buildings do not flood.

means.word_mean: 1. a column of wood or steel or concrete that is driven into the ground to provide support for a structure
